  <span id="freeText8462332465813173855" style="display:none">Enjoyed this one. You know the ending (the fictitious depiction of the real-life death of Pakistan's President General Zia) from the very beginning. The alternate chapters work well of the General and his cohorts mixed with those of the Air Force cadet Shigri who is planning to assassinate the President thereby avenging the death of his father. It's a fast paced satire of the Pakistan-US relationship at the end of the 80s. The cameo of Bill Casey the CIA Director was a highlight as was the ongoing depiction of Zia obsession about his own safety and the scheming of the Generals to replace Zia.</span>
