<div id="review_2423438709" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2423438709" />
    <a title="اُمامہ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50052704"><img alt="اُمامہ " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2423438709?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="اُمامہ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="اُمامہ " href="/user/show/50052704">اُمامہ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9788184001891" href="/book/show/16041424-a-case-of-exploding-mangoes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=politics">politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=pakistan">pakistan</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=military">military</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2423438709" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer189316120514574300">A good political satire. Mohammed Hanif has torn into the corruption of the army and General Zia’s dictatorship. He has in-depth taken the world through the minutes and the depths of the state of affairs prevailing in the country at that time. This book tells the story of a Pakistani Air Force officer, Ali, who wants to avenge the death of his father. The official story is that his father committed suicide but Ali believes the official story to be a lie. He knows that his father was murdered. So</span>
  <span id="freeText189316120514574300" style="display:none">A good political satire. Mohammed Hanif has torn into the corruption of the army and General Zia’s dictatorship. He has in-depth taken the world through the minutes and the depths of the state of affairs prevailing in the country at that time. This book tells the story of a Pakistani Air Force officer, Ali, who wants to avenge the death of his father. The official story is that his father committed suicide but Ali believes the official story to be a lie. He knows that his father was murdered. So he plots the ultimate revenge: the assassination of the President of Pakistan, Zia-ul-Haq.<br />The humor is crazy, sometimes sophomoric, always amusing. The novel spends much time exposing the stupidity, brutality and hypocrisy of Pakistan's military rulers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="189316120514574300" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


