<div id="review_3942702994" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3942702994" />
    <a title="Savera" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/79259835-savera"><img alt="Savera" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533483778p2/79259835.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3942702994?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Savera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Savera" href="/user/show/79259835-savera">Savera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3942702994" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5912601203689415948">Books like this are important as they foster curiosity in historical and political events. I personally didn&apos;t know the extent of the involvement of Middle Eastern countries in the Cold War. <br/><br/>As George Santayana (writer &amp; philosopher) said: &apos;Those who do not learn history are doomed to repeat it.&apos;<br/>Mohammed Hanif clearly understands the importance of this quote.<br/><br/>The narrative jumped around, but never lost me. The author has a way of hooking you, so that you can&apos;t help but follow every side character</span>
  <span id="freeText5912601203689415948" style="display:none">Books like this are important as they foster curiosity in historical and political events. I personally didn't know the extent of the involvement of Middle Eastern countries in the Cold War. <br /><br />As George Santayana (writer &amp; philosopher) said: 'Those who do not learn history are doomed to repeat it.'<br />Mohammed Hanif clearly understands the importance of this quote.<br /><br />The narrative jumped around, but never lost me. The author has a way of hooking you, so that you can't help but follow every side characters' story as if they were the main focus of the book.<br /><br />Ali Shigri, as a main character, was likeable and realistic, even in his darkest hours. His relationships with his fellow soldiers, superiors, and family name, made the book an unforgettable experience.<br /><br />Funny, sad, philosophical, and daringly controversial in its topic, I will remember A Case of Exploding Mangoes for years to come. <br /><br />Recommended to those who enjoyed 'Q&amp;A' (Slumdog Millionaire) - Vikas Swarup, and 'The Kite Runner' - Khaled Hosseini.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5912601203689415948" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


